[{"id":"0316d3f351d81860bf9656df15f8a269","from":"Lesley Groff","from_email":"lesley@nysgllc.com","to":"J. Epstein","to_list":[{"name":"J. Epstein","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"FW: jeffrey's puppy","date":"2007-10-04T17:45:34.000Z","formatted_date":"Oct 4, 2007","formatted_time":"5:45 PM","body":" \n\n \n\nFrom: Noital4u@aol.com [mailto:Noital4u@aol.com] \nSent: Thursday, October 04, 2007 1:25 PM\nTo: Lesley Groff\nSubject: Re: jeffrey's puppy\n\n \n\nHi Lesley,\n\n \n\nJanet made the phone call this morning to her friend that breeds English\nSpringers.  The wheels are turning and I have my hopes up that we will\nfind a puppy for Jeffrey.  I know how excited he gets, I hate to let him\ndown. Also, my friend Pepper Frazier is having lunch today with the vice\nchairman of Westminster Kennel Club.  I asked Pepper to find out if he\nhas any ideas for Springer breeders. \n\n \n\nI hope you don't think I am a spoiled brat for trying to have Jamie with\nus in NYC.  As I said to you, everything happens for a reason.  I'm sure\nit will be best for Jamie to be closer to the show grounds and in the\nmix.  I am very grateful for the use of Jeffrey's apartments.  He's a\ngood guy!\n\n \n\nI hope to meet you during my visit.  It would be fun to have you come\nsee Jamie show.  This is an exciting time!\n\n \n\nPamela\n\n \n\n \n\n\n\n\n\n________________________________\n\nSee what's new at AOL.com <http://www.aol.com?NCID=AOLCMP00300000001170>\nand Make AOL Your Homepage\n<http://www.aol.com/mksplash.adp?NCID=AOLCMP00300000001169> .\n\n","body_html":"<html xmlns:v=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:vml\" xmlns:o=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office\" xmlns:w=\"urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word\" xmlns:m=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/office/2004/12/omml\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40\">\n\n<head>\n<META HTTP-EQUIV=\"Content-Type\" CONTENT=\"text/html; charset=us-ascii\">\n<meta name=Generator content=\"Microsoft Word 12 (filtered medium)\"